wondering what to do next.

00:44:24.780 --> 00:44:26.120
It's muscle memory.

00:44:26.120 --> 00:44:28.520
It's a habit.

00:44:28.520 --> 00:44:30.530
This is the trigger or cue--

00:44:30.530 --> 00:44:33.350
picking up my toothbrush
is the trigger or cue

00:44:33.350 --> 00:44:37.970
that precedes the next immediate
action, which is picking up

00:44:37.970 --> 00:44:40.250
that tube of toothpaste.

00:44:40.250 --> 00:44:44.660
And so in order to form a
habit, things to be conscious

00:44:44.660 --> 00:44:47.300
of-- and this comes from Charles
Duhigg in his book "The Power

00:44:47.300 --> 00:44:48.200
of Habit"--

00:44:48.200 --> 00:44:53.660
is time, location,
immediately preceding action,

00:44:53.660 --> 00:44:54.780
emotional state.

00:44:54.780 --> 00:44:55.280
Right?

00:44:55.280 --> 00:44:56.810
And if there's a
particular habit

00:44:56.810 --> 00:44:58.610
that you're trying to break--

00:44:58.610 --> 00:45:00.440
he gave the example
of he would always

00:45:00.440 --> 00:45:03.740
get up and start, around 3:30 in
the afternoon, he would get up,

00:45:03.740 --> 00:45:05.270
and he would eat a cookie.

00:45:05.270 --> 00:45:06.470
And he just kept doing this.

00:45:06.470 --> 00:45:07.803
And then he kept eating cookies.

00:45:07.803 --> 00:45:10.070
And he started gaining weight.

00:45:10.070 --> 00:45:14.660
And so then he noted the time.

00:45:14.660 --> 00:45:15.660
He noted the location.

00:45:15.660 --> 00:45:18.230
He noted the emotional
state that he was in,

00:45:18.230 --> 00:45:20.830
which was kind of bored
or restless or wanting

00:45:20.830 --> 00:45:23.220
a break around that time.

00:45:23.220 --> 00:45:26.900
And he was able
to replace getting

00:45:26.900 --> 00:45:31.760
a cookie with just taking
a walk and, you know,

00:45:31.760 --> 00:45:33.950
satisfying that emotional
state, satisfying

00:45:33.950 --> 00:45:35.930
the state of like
boredom restlessness

00:45:35.930 --> 00:45:37.730
without the cookie.

00:45:37.730 --> 00:45:41.720
So he kept the cue or
trigger, and then he

00:45:41.720 --> 00:45:45.080
kept the reward, which
was the satisfaction

00:45:45.080 --> 00:45:49.490
of his restlessness, like that
entertainment and distraction.

00:45:49.490 --> 00:45:51.300
And he replaced the
action in the middle.

00:45:51.300 --> 00:45:53.750
So if you break down
a habit into cue,

00:45:53.750 --> 00:45:56.630
action, reward,
then keep the cue.

00:45:56.630 --> 00:45:58.040
Keep the reward.

00:45:58.040 --> 00:45:59.900
Switch out the action.

00:45:59.900 --> 00:46:03.020
There's this notion also
called habit stacking.

00:46:03.020 --> 00:46:08.000
And that is to build habits
on top of other habits.

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:13.430
And so the reason that
habit stacking works so well

00:46:13.430 --> 00:46:17.390
is, because every habit
needs a given cue,

00:46:17.390 --> 00:46:20.360
if you have a cue already
because that cue is

00:46:20.360 --> 00:46:22.250
a habit that you're
already doing,

00:46:22.250 --> 00:46:24.380
then, since you're
already doing it,

00:46:24.380 --> 00:46:28.080
you know that you can stack
another habit on top of that.

00:46:28.080 --> 00:46:31.670
So for example, every morning
I make a cup of coffee.

00:46:31.670 --> 00:46:33.770
Earlier this year,
I decided that I

00:46:33.770 --> 00:46:37.260
wanted to create a habit
of writing in a journal.

00:46:37.260 --> 00:46:41.660
And so I now stack my
journal writing habit

00:46:41.660 --> 00:46:43.160
with my coffee habit.

00:46:43.160 --> 00:46:45.890
I will never forget to
drink coffee in the morning.

00:46:45.890 --> 00:46:48.180
That's impossible.

00:46:48.180 --> 00:46:50.330
And so when I have
that cup of coffee,

00:46:50.330 --> 00:46:54.320
that is now the cue or the
trigger that tells me time

00:46:54.320 --> 00:46:56.420
to write in a journal.

00:46:56.420 --> 00:46:59.240
And then the next habit
that I will form--

00:46:59.240 --> 00:47:02.400
and it's typically most
effective to only form

00:47:02.400 --> 00:47:03.590
one habit at a time.

00:47:03.590 --> 00:47:06.920
A lot of people try to stack
on too many habits all at once.

00:47:06.920 --> 00:47:08.720
And then the whole
thing collapses.

00:47:08.720 --> 00:47:10.880
So choose one habit.

00:47:10.880 --> 00:47:13.190
For me, it was
writing in my journal.

00:47:13.190 --> 00:47:16.290
Stick with that
for 30 to 60 days.

00:47:16.290 --> 00:47:19.320
And then at the end of that,
then add in another one.

00:47:19.320 --> 00:47:21.713
So right now, it's
the end of February.

